Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
fix_drc_with_patch(25.10)                            fix_drc_with_patch(25.10)

Name
       fix_drc_with_patch  -  Fixes  violations by adding trims/patches in the
       whole design, including fixed cell objects, pre-routed nets,  and  spe-
       cial nets on a pre-route database

Syntax
       fix_drc_with_patch

       [-help]

       [<area>]

       [-include_passive_fill]

       [-layer_range <bottomLayer>:<topLayer>]

       Fixes violations by adding trims/patches in the whole design, including
       fixed  cell  objects,  pre-routed nets, and special nets on a pre-route
       database. You can use this command after floorplanning  the  design  or
       after  PG  routing or on pre-routed routing database, however, you must
       use it before running routeDesign.

       Note: Cadence recommends you to use the  fix_drc_with_patch command for
       sign-off checks on pre-route database. It should not be used  for  flow
       continuation.

Parameters
       <area> Enables  the  tool to trim/add patches and fix DRC violations in
              the specified route area. You can specify the area using the  x1
              y1 x2 y2 coordinate values.

              Data_type: box, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each fix_drc_with_patch parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man fix_drc_with_patch

       -include_passive_fill
              Performs passive fill insertion after fixing DRC violations.

              Data_type: box, optional

       -layer_range <bottomLayer:topLayer>
              Enables the tool to trim/add  patches  and  fix  DRC  violations
              within the specified layer range (<bottomLayer>:<topLayer>).

              Data_type:  string, optional

Examples
       The  following command adds patches and fixes DRC violations within the
       2:4 layer range:

       fix_drc_with_patch -layer_range <2:4>

